705298f-c.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Tilden Avenue
705298f-c.text:
(1)
King's Highway, at the S.E. corner of Tilden Ave., showing the Flatlands Neck Sabbath Church. The congregation of this Church were incorporated in 1867. Originally it was a Sabbath School, and it was established by John Remsen on land donated by him to the people of the
'Neck".
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, at a later date.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same as No. 2, from another angle. Because of the widening of King's Highway, the building will be moved.back.to the new curb line.,
March 1925.
Euiene L. Armbruster Collaction.
